1. copy edges.md and images folder to a local folder, 
2. navigate to that folder in a terminal
3. > pandoc edge.md --latex-engine=xelatex -V margin-left=2.5cm -V margin-right=2.5cm -f markdown-implicit_figures  -o edge.pdf

* The --latex-engine=xelatex option changes the default latex engine to generate the PDF; as the default one can't handle accents.
* The -V margin options allows us to customize the margins to be 2.5cm wide (the default is closer to 5 or 6 cm).
* The -f markdown-implicit_figures suppresses the XeLaTeX default behaviour of autoamtically numerating the figures.


This can be done on any computer in the CREMI.
To be used on your own computer, you must first install Pandoc and the XeLaTeX engine.

This procedure respects the automatic enumeration of references given in Taveau's email.
